      <akn:section eId="sec_50_2201_04d">
        <akn:num>50-2201.04d</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Bicyclists’ use of leading pedestrian intervals.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_50-2201_04d_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>A bicyclist may cross at an intersection while following the pedestrian traffic control signal for the bicyclist’s direction of travel unless otherwise directed by traffic signs or traffic control devices.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_50-2201_04d_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>A bicyclist may cross an intersection where a leading pedestrian interval is used.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
